-- Liverpool Wants Aston Villa's Ashley Young for $24 Million: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2010-12-09T09:14:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-09/liverpool-wants-aston-villa-s-ashley-young-for-24-million-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Liverpool Targets Young  Liverpool is planning to sign Aston Villa’s  Ashley Young 
for 15 million pounds ($23.7 million) in next month’s transfer
window, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Sources at Liverpool are “quietly confident” the Reds can
reach a deal with Villa if the England winger agrees to the move,
according to the Mirror.  Reds Want Right Back  Liverpool is “closing in” on Rennes right back Rod Fanni,
raising doubts about the future of England international  Glen Johnson , the  Daily Mirror  said.  Fanni would cost 3 million pounds, according to the Mirror.
Tottenham is among teams interested in signing Johnson if he
becomes available, the newspaper reported.  Villa’s Keane Bid  Aston Villa is to bid 6 million pounds for Tottenham
striker  Robbie Keane , the  Daily Mail  reported.  Keane has held talks with Spurs about leaving and Villa
coach  Gerard Houllier  will “move swiftly” to conclude a deal,
according to the Mail.  West Ham, Wolves and Celtic also want to sign Keane,
according to the  Daily Star .  Beckham Says No  Leicester coach Sven-Goran Eriksson said  David Beckham 
rejected an offer to join the second-tier Championship team on
loan,  the Sun  reported.  Eriksson also unsuccessfully tried to add Tottenham’s Keane
and Manchester City’s  Roque Santa Cruz  as he seeks a “big name
signing” next month, the Sun said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Duff  in Madrid at 
 aduff4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
